      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Movie Business</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Creative Artists Agency senior literary agent Robert Bookman letter on Rick Lyman's May 7 article on Hollywood 'wheeler dealer' Sammy Glick recalls statement by Hollywood attorney Martin Gang that 'The movie business is just like every other business. Only more so.'</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Reading Rick Lyman's discourse on the so-called ''Hollywood wheeler-dealer'' [''The Long Run of Sammy Glick,'' May 7] brought to mind an ironic comment by the great Martin Gang, who was arguably the first important Hollywood attorney. He said: ''The movie business is just like every other business. Only more so.''</p>
        <p>ROBERT BOOKMAN  Beverly Hills, Calif.</p>
        <p>The writer is a senior literary agent at Creative Artists Agency.</p>
      </block>
